    script: "Good morning. Residents in the Westdale and Riverside neighbourhoods of Burlington are facing a water service disruption following a major water main break that occurred overnight. The break, located on Glenwood Avenue near Parkside Drive, has left approximately forty-two hundred households without running water as crews work to contain the damage.\n\nThe water main, installed in nineteen eighty-three, ruptured at approximately two fifteen AM. Burlington Public Works Director Rachel Huang says the department became aware when pressure monitoring systems detected a sudden drop in water pressure across the affected zone. Crews were on site within the hour.\n\nResidents in the affected area are asked not to use their taps for drinking, cooking, or bathing until further notice. The city is distributing bottled water at three temporary stations: Westdale Community Centre on Mill Road, Riverside Arena on Lakeview Boulevard, and the Elmwood Public Library on King Street. Each household may collect up to two cases per visit.\n\nDirector Huang says crews are working around the clock and expect to restore service to most of the area by tomorrow evening, though some homes may experience low pressure or discoloured water for up to forty-eight hours after service resumes. Residents are advised to run their cold taps for several minutes before using water for drinking or cooking once service is restored.\n\nUpdates will be posted every four hours on the city's website at burlington.ca.",
