    desc: "You will hear a discussion between three people. Listen carefully and answer the questions.",
    videoScene: "<h4>🎬 Video Scene Description</h4><p>Three educators — Mr. Park, Mrs. Allen, and Ms. Ortega — are seated around a rectangular table in a school staffroom. A whiteboard behind them shows 'ROM Trip — March 14.' Mr. Park has a clipboard. Mrs. Allen is typing on a laptop. Ms. Ortega holds a printed flyer from the Royal Ontario Museum.</p>",
    script: "Mr. Park: OK, we've confirmed the Royal Ontario Museum trip for March fourteenth. We have ninety-three grade seven students going, and we need to finalize logistics today. Mrs. Allen, can you start with transportation?\n\nMrs. Allen: I've contacted the transportation company. They can provide two fifty-passenger coaches. That gives us enough room for all students plus chaperones. The cost is four hundred and fifty dollars per bus — nine hundred dollars total.\n\nMr. Park: Can we ask parents to cover the full amount, or does the school cover part?\n\nMrs. Allen: The school's activity fund covers up to three hundred dollars. That leaves six hundred divided among the students — roughly six-fifty each.\n\nMs. Ortega: I'd round that up to seven dollars per student to give us a small buffer. Also, the museum offers two options for school groups. Option A is general admission at nine-fifty per student. Option B is twelve dollars and includes a guided tour of the Ancient Egypt and Indigenous Canada exhibits.\n\nMr. Park: Option B sounds more educational — we're covering both ancient civilizations and Canadian Indigenous history this term. I'd go with the guided tour.\n\nMrs. Allen: So total per student is seven dollars transportation plus twelve dollars admission — nineteen dollars.\n\nMs. Ortega: We also need one adult chaperone per ten students. So at least ten chaperones. I have three parent volunteers confirmed. Do either of you have more?\n\nMr. Park: I have four confirmed, and Mrs. Chen said she'd join as well.\n\nMrs. Allen: I can bring two more. That's ten total — perfect.\n\nMr. Park: Great. I'll send permission forms and payment packages home this Friday.",
